# Government Tender Announcement

## Solicitation for Information Technology Consultation Services

**Government of Canada Tender Notice**

The Department of Public Works and Government Services on behalf of the Department of National Defence invites bids from qualified service providers for the provision of Information Technology Consultation Services. This solicitation is being issued under the Task-Based Informatics Professional Services (TBIPS) Supply Arrangement (SA) method of supply.

### Service Requirements
The successful bidder will provide various IT services, including:

1. Storage Architect
2. System Administrator
3. Technical Writer
4. Webmaster

### Duration of Contract
The contract will be for a period of three years, with two one-year irrevocable options to extend the term. The bid submission deadline is November 29, 2023 at 14:00 PM EST. Late bids will not be accepted.

### Eligibility Criteria
Only Indigenous TBIPS SA Holders holding a TBIPS SA for Tier 2 at the time of bid closing, in all required resource categories in this solicitation and in the National Capital Region under the EN578-170432 series of SAs are eligible to compete.

### Procurement Strategy for Indigenous Business
This procurement is set aside under the federal government’s Procurement Strategy for Indigenous Business.

### Contracting Entity
The contracting entity for this solicitation is the Department of Public Works and Government Services. The contact person is Kelly, James (SPAC/PSPC), who can be reached at james.kelly@tpsgc-pwgsc.gc.ca.
